\cf0 IdentitySample contains a search field allowing you to filter identities by name.  This is accomplished by using CSIdentityQueryCreateForName.  When the search field is empty, you'll see all the identities on the system.  These are the same identities that appear in the Accounts Pref Pane.  If you delete an identity in IdentitySample, you'll also be deleting the login account for that identity (their home folder won't be deleted).  After an identity is selected in the sidebar, the identity information is fetched and displayed.  You can change various attributes of the identity like full name, e-mail, add/remove aliases, and then commit your changes by clicking the Apply button which calls CSIdentityCommit.  Add new identities to the system by clicking the add button beneath the sidebar and fill in the required information.  Remove identities by selecting an identity in the sidebar and then clicking remove.\
